WEBVTT

00:22.140 --> 00:23.100
CHAPTER IV.

00:23.380 --> 00:28.320
After a return to the prison, a surfer was found to be in a state of nervous excitement

00:28.320 --> 00:33.980
that demanded constant watchfulness, lest she should perpetrate violence on herself

00:33.980 --> 00:37.360
or do some half-francid mischief to the poor babe.

00:38.280 --> 00:43.420
As night approached, it proving impossible to quell her insubordination by rebuke of

00:43.420 --> 00:48.920
threats of punishment, Master Brackett, the jailer, thought fit to introduce a physician.

00:50.120 --> 00:54.660
He described him as a man of skill in all Christian modes of physical science,

00:54.660 --> 01:00.980
and likewise familiar with whatever the savage people could teach in respect to medicinal herbs

01:00.980 --> 01:07.060
and roots that grew in the forest. To say the truth, there was much need of professional

01:07.060 --> 01:13.760
assistance, not merely for Esther herself, but still more urgently for the child, who,

01:14.040 --> 01:19.460
drawing his sustenance from the maternal bosom, seemed to have drunk in it with all the turmoil,

01:19.460 --> 01:23.380
the anguish and despair which pervaded the mother's system.

01:24.200 --> 01:28.380
It now breathed in convulsions of pain, and was a forcible type,

01:28.680 --> 01:33.680
in its little frame of the moral agony which Esther Pryne had borne throughout the day.

01:35.000 --> 01:39.360
Closely following the jailer into the dismal apartment, appeared that individual,

01:39.820 --> 01:44.640
a singular aspect whose presence in the crowd had been of such steep interest to the wearer

01:44.640 --> 01:50.040
of the scarlet letter. He was lodged in the prison, not as suspected of any offence,

01:50.760 --> 01:55.700
but as the most convenient and suitable mode of disposing of him, until the magistrate

01:55.700 --> 02:01.340
should have conferred with Indian seshamores respecting his ransom. His name was announced

02:01.340 --> 02:07.760
as Roger Schillingworth. The jailer, after hushering him into the room, remained a moment,

02:08.300 --> 02:14.080
marveling at comparative quiet that followed his entrance, for Esther Pryne had immediately

02:14.080 --> 02:18.080
become as still as death, although the child continued to moan.

02:18.980 --> 02:23.980
''Pry thee, friend, leave me alone with my patients,'' said the practitioner.

02:24.920 --> 02:30.860
''Trust me, good jailer, you shall briefly have peace in your house, and, I promise you,

02:31.160 --> 02:37.840
Mistress Pryne shall be more amiable to just authority than you may have found her here before.''

02:39.860 --> 02:45.020
''Nay, if your horseship can accomplish that,'' answered Master Brackett,

02:45.500 --> 02:52.380
''I shall own you for a man of skill indeed. Fairly, do man hath been like a possessed one,

02:52.620 --> 02:57.440
and there lacks little that I should take in hand to drive Satan out of her with stripes.''

02:58.860 --> 03:03.360
The stranger that entered the room had a characteristic quietitude of the profession

03:03.360 --> 03:09.280
to which he announced himself as belonging. Nor did this demeanor change when the withdrawal

03:09.280 --> 03:15.080
of the prison keeper left him face to face with the woman, whose observed notice of him in the

03:15.080 --> 03:22.180
crowd had intimated so close a relation between himself and her. His first care was given to the

03:22.180 --> 03:29.340
child, whose cries, indeed, as she lay reading on the trundled bed, made it a peremptory necessity

03:29.340 --> 03:35.280
to postpone all other business to the task of suiting her. He examined the infant carefully,

03:35.680 --> 03:40.880
and then proceeded to unclasp a leathern case, which he took from the niece's dress.

03:41.780 --> 03:47.160
It appeared to contain medical preparations, one of which he mingled with a cup of water.

03:48.560 --> 03:55.740
''My old studies in alchemy,'' absurd he, ''and my sojourn, for above a year past,

03:55.740 --> 04:01.120
among a pupil well versed in the kindly properties of simples, have made a better

04:01.120 --> 04:07.600
physician of me than many that claimed medical degree. Here, woman, the child is yours,

04:07.880 --> 04:14.880
she is none of mine. Neither will she recognize my voice or aspect as a father's. Administer this

04:14.880 --> 04:22.860
drug, therefore, with thine own hand.'' As to repel the offered medicine, at the same time,

04:22.860 --> 04:26.020
he gave me to strongly mark the prehension into his face.

04:26.760 --> 04:31.220
''Wouldst thou avenge thyself on the innocent babe?'' whispered she.

04:32.640 --> 04:37.340
''Foolish woman,'' responded the physician, half coldly, half soothingly.

04:38.380 --> 04:44.180
''What should hail me to harm this misbegotten and miserable babe? The medicine is potent for good,

04:44.760 --> 04:50.560
and were it my child, yeah, my own, as well as thine, I could do no better for it.''

04:51.800 --> 04:58.020
As she still hesitated, being in fact in so reasonable a state of mind, he took the infant

04:58.020 --> 05:04.800
in his arms and himself administered the drug. It soon proved his efficacy, and redeemed Litch's

05:04.800 --> 05:12.200
pledge. The mounted little patient subsided, its convulsive tossing gradually ceased, and in a few

05:12.200 --> 05:18.480
moments, as is the custom of young children after relief from pain, it sank into a profound and dewy

05:18.480 --> 05:25.100
slumber. The physician, as he had a fair right to be turned, next bestowed his attention on the

05:25.100 --> 05:32.460
mother. With calm and intense scrutiny, he felt her pulse, looked into her eyes, a gaze that made

05:32.460 --> 05:39.620
her heart shrink and shudder, because so familiar, and yet so strange and cold, and, finally,

05:40.020 --> 05:44.040
satisfied with his investigation, proceeded to mingle another drug.

05:45.820 --> 05:52.240
''I know not left nor in the panthe,'' remarked he, ''but I have learned many new secrets in the

05:52.240 --> 05:58.720
wilderness, and here is one of them, a recipe that an Indian taught me, in the quiet of some lessons

05:58.720 --> 06:05.740
of my own, that was all asparacelsus. Drink it. It may be less soothing than a sinless conscience,

06:06.040 --> 06:12.920
that I cannot give thee, but it will come to swell and heaving of thy passion, like oil thrown on the

06:12.920 --> 06:21.140
tempestuous sea.'' He presented the cup to Esther, who received it with a slow, earnest look into

06:21.140 --> 06:27.280
his face, not precisely a look of fear, yet full of doubt and questioning as to what his purpose

06:27.280 --> 06:36.160
might be. She looked also at her slumbering child. ''I have thought of death,'' said she,

06:36.160 --> 06:40.220
''I have wished for it, would even have prayed for it,

06:40.440 --> 06:46.740
retweeted such as I should pray for anything. Yet, if death be in this cup,

06:47.140 --> 06:53.900
I bid thee think again, here thy behold is me coiffed. See, it is even now at my lips.''

06:55.340 --> 06:59.760
''Drink, then,'' replied he, still with the same cool composure.

07:00.740 --> 07:06.660
''Thus thou know me so little, Esther Prine, or my purposes won't be so shallow.

07:07.360 --> 07:12.500
Even if I imagine a scheme of vengeance, what could I do better for my object than to let thy

07:12.500 --> 07:19.800
live, than to give thy medicines against all harm and peril of life, so that this burning shame may

07:19.800 --> 07:26.820
still blaze upon thy bosom?'' As he spoke, he laid his long forefinger on scarlet leather,

07:26.820 --> 07:33.880
which her width seemed scorched into Esther's breast, as if it had been red hot. He noticed

07:33.880 --> 07:40.660
that her involuntarily gestured and smiled. ''Leave, therefore, and bear about thy doom with thee,

07:40.880 --> 07:46.420
in the eyes of men and women, in the eyes of him whom thou didst call thy husband,

07:46.900 --> 07:52.560
in the eyes of yonder child, and, that thou mayest live, take off this drug.''

07:54.340 --> 08:01.160
Without further exhalation or delay, Esther Prine drained the cup, and, at notion of demand of skill,

08:01.740 --> 08:07.140
seated herself on the bed, where the child was sleeping, while he drew the only chair

08:07.140 --> 08:13.420
which the room afforded, and took his own seat beside her. She could not but tremble at these

08:13.420 --> 08:21.300
preparations, for she felt that, having now done all that humanity or principle, or, if so it were,

08:21.300 --> 08:26.100
a refined cruelty impaled him to do for the life of physical suffering,

08:26.680 --> 08:31.840
he was next to treat with her as the man whom she had most deeply and irreparably injured.

08:33.960 --> 08:42.660
''Hester,'' said he, ''I ask not wherefore, nor how, thou hast fallen into the pits, or, say,

08:42.920 --> 08:49.840
rather, thou hast ascended to the pedestal of infamy on which I found thee. The reason is not

08:49.840 --> 08:57.140
hard to seek. It was my folly and thy weakness. I, a man of thought, the bookwarden of great

08:57.140 --> 09:03.440
labouries, a man already in decay, having given my best years to feed the hungry dream of knowledge,

09:04.220 --> 09:10.600
what had I to do with youth and beauty like thine own? Mishappen from my birth hour. How

09:10.600 --> 09:17.180
could I delude myself with the idea that intellectual gifts might reveal physical deformity in a young

09:17.180 --> 09:25.620
girl's fantasy? Men call me wise. If sages were ever wise in their own behove, I might have foreseen

09:25.620 --> 09:32.020
all this. I might have known that, as I came out of the vast and dismal forest and entered this

09:32.020 --> 09:37.260
settlement of Christian men, the very first object to meet my eyes would be thyself,

09:37.460 --> 09:47.160
Hester Pryne, standing up, a statue of ignominy before the people. Nay, from the moment when he

09:47.160 --> 09:53.540
gathered, a married pair, I might have beheld the bell-fire of that scarlet letter blazing at

09:53.540 --> 10:02.200
the end of our path. Thou knowest, said Hester, for, depressed as she was, she could not endure

10:02.200 --> 10:17.140
this last quiet step at the token of her shame. Thou knowest that I was frank with thee. I felt

10:17.140 --> 10:23.800
but, up to that epoch of my life, I had lived in vain. The world had been so cheerless.

10:24.340 --> 10:30.180
My heart was a habitation large enough for many guests, but lonely and chill, and without the

10:30.180 --> 10:38.600
household fire. I longed to kindle one. It seemed not so wild a dream, old as I was, and sombre as

10:38.600 --> 10:46.080
I was, and mishappen as I was. That simple bliss, which is scattered far and wide, for all mankind

10:46.080 --> 10:54.320
to gather up, might yet be mine. And so, Hester, I drew thee into my heart, into its innermost

10:54.320 --> 10:59.160
chamber, and thought to warm thee by the warmth which thy presence made there.

11:00.660 --> 11:10.960
I have greatly wronged thee, murmured Hester. We have wronged each other, answered he. Mine was

11:10.960 --> 11:16.580
wrong, when I betrayed thy putting youth into a false and unnatural relation with my decay.

11:17.300 --> 11:22.620
Therefore, as a man who has not thought and philosophied in vain, I seek no vengeance,

11:23.120 --> 11:28.920
plot no evil against thee. Between thee and me, the scale hangs fairly balanced.

11:29.540 --> 11:35.040
But, Hester, the man leaves who has wronged us both. Who is he?

11:36.120 --> 11:44.040
Ask me not, replied Hester Pryne, looking firmly into his face. That thou shalt never know.

11:45.820 --> 11:52.180
Never, sayest thou? Rejoin he with a smile of dark and self-relying intelligence.

11:53.000 --> 11:59.720
Never know him. Believe me, Hester, there are few things, whether in the outward world, or,

11:59.720 --> 12:05.500
to a certain depth, in the invisible sphere of thought, few things hidden from the man

12:05.500 --> 12:12.420
who devotes himself earnestly and unreservedly to the solution of a mystery. Thou mayest cover

12:12.420 --> 12:19.740
up thy secret from the Pryme Altitude. Thou mayest conceal it, too, from ministers and magistrates,

12:20.280 --> 12:25.100
even as thou didst this day, when they sought to wrench the name out of thy heart,

12:25.100 --> 12:31.820
and give thee a partner on thy pedestal. But, as for me, I come to the inquest with other

12:31.820 --> 12:37.060
senses than they possess. I shall seek this man, as I have thought through sin books,

12:37.420 --> 12:42.760
as I have sought goals in alchemy. There is a sympathy that will make me conscious of him.

12:43.220 --> 12:50.140
I shall see him tremble. I shall feel myself shudder suddenly and unwares. Sooner or later,

12:50.140 --> 12:57.180
he must needs be mine. The eyes of the wrinkled scholar glowed so intensely upon her

12:57.180 --> 13:00.800
that, as to Pryne, clasped her hand over her heart,

13:01.140 --> 13:07.220
dreading lest he should read secret there at once. Thou wilt not reveal his name.

13:08.120 --> 13:15.120
Not lest he is mine, resumed he, with a look of confidence, as if destiny were at one with him.

13:15.700 --> 13:19.960
He bears no layer of infamy wrought into his garment, as thou dost,

13:20.400 --> 13:26.640
but I shall read it on his heart. Yet fear not for him. Think not that I shall interfere

13:26.640 --> 13:32.980
with heaven's own method of retribution, or, to my own loss, betray him to the grip of human love.

13:34.060 --> 13:40.280
Neither do thou imagine that I shall contrive hard against his life, no, nor against his fame,

13:40.280 --> 13:47.720
if, as I judge, he be a man of fair repute. Let him live. Let him hide himself in outward

13:47.720 --> 13:51.640
honour, if he may. Not lest he shall be mine.

13:53.040 --> 14:00.200
Thy acts are like mercy, said Esther, bewildered and appalled, but thy words interpret thee as a

14:00.200 --> 14:09.220
terror. One thing. Thou that was my life, I wouldn't join upon thee, continued the scholar.

14:09.860 --> 14:17.180
Thou hast kept secret of thy paramour. Keep likewise mine. There are none in this land that

14:17.180 --> 14:24.100
know me. Bring not to any human soul that thou didst ever call me husband. Here, on this wild

14:24.100 --> 14:30.900
outskirt of the earth, I shall pitch my tent. For, elsewhere a wanderer and isolated from human

14:30.900 --> 14:37.640
interests, I find here a woman, a man, a child, amongst whom and myself there exists the closest

14:37.640 --> 14:45.200
ligaments, no matter whether of love or hate, no matter whether of right or wrong. Thou and thine,

14:45.680 --> 14:52.480
Esther Pryne, belong to me. My home is where thou art and where he is. But betray me not.

14:54.760 --> 15:01.640
Wherefore dost thou desire it? inquired Esther, shrinking, she hardly knew why, from the secret

15:01.640 --> 15:06.880
bound. Why not denounce thyself openly and cast me off at once?

15:08.560 --> 15:13.980
It may be, he replied, because I will not encounter the dishonour that

15:14.580 --> 15:21.420
besmirches the husband of a faithless woman. It may be for other reasons. Enough. It is my purpose

15:21.420 --> 15:27.260
to live and die unknown. Let therefore thy husband be to the world as one already dead,

15:27.260 --> 15:34.200
and of whom no tidings shall ever come. Recognise me not by word, by sign, by look.

15:34.960 --> 15:41.120
Breed not the secret above all to the man thou houghtest of. Should thou fail me in this,

15:41.440 --> 15:47.760
beware. His fame, his position, his life will be in my hands. Beware.

15:48.520 --> 15:58.460
I'll keep thy secret, and I have his, said Esther, swear it, rejoin he, and she took to oath.

15:59.840 --> 16:05.960
And now, Mistress Pryne, said old Roger Chillingworth, as he was hereafter to be

16:05.960 --> 16:13.720
named, I leave thee alone, alone with thy infant and scarlet letter. Who is it, Esther,

16:13.720 --> 16:17.720
doth thou sentence by indeed to wear the token in thy sleep?

16:18.480 --> 16:21.540
Art thou not afraid of nightmares and hideous dreams?

16:23.040 --> 16:29.380
Why dost thou smile so at me? inquired Esther, troubled at the expression of his eyes.

16:30.380 --> 16:34.800
Art thou like the black man that hunts the forest round about us,

16:35.320 --> 16:38.860
as thou entice me into a bond that will prove the ruin of my soul?

16:39.900 --> 16:45.880
Not thy soul, he answered with another smile. No, not thine.

